name: Lake Country Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: Go in the front door, past the minister's door, and immediately turn right into the office area. Restroom is straight ahead and ADA compliant. Fully scooter accessible
comment: If the church is open you are welcome. There are also gendered bathrooms in the back hall, 2 stalls to the Women's and 1 stall 1 urinal to the Men's- these are labeled with a large sign in the hallway reminding people to pick any bathroom which suits their personal gender presentation, and to be respectful of other's choices. Minister's name and cell number are posted outside of the building by the front door- if you are having an emergency related to your trans* status, please call and she will come and let you in or get you help, even if the building is locked. She lives very close.

comment: wesley is a spiritual community committed to providing safe space for lgbtq folk, people of all genders, gender nonconforming folk.  a lot of people stop by for a cup of coffee, place to study, place to rest, place to talk.  there's often programming, but don't worry about just heading to the restroom!
